==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Margarin
<hw>Mar"ga*rin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>margarine</ets>. See <er>Margarite</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A fatty substance, extracted from animal fats and
certain vegetable oils, formerly supposed to be a definite compound of
glycerin and margaric acid, but now known to be simply a mixture or
combination of tristearin and tripalmitin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Margarine</ent>⟦br⟧
